Defendant Wesley R Bynum in court with attorney Syovata Kanini Edari.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.
BRANCH 17 FOR BRANCH 3.
 Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1-
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to any sentence; release for work (if working), inmate work assignments, The Day Reporting Center (if eligible) and school; credit for 0 days. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. 

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 12 MONTHS  with the following conditions:

- Maintain Absolute Sobriety.
- No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment including drug and alcohol testing. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
- Defendant may not live where a firearm is kept. 
- Continue  with regularly participation in an HSED or GED program until completed then maintain full time work and/or school . 
- Defendant to not associate with any known gang member, associate or affiliate. 
- No contact with any known illegal drug user.
- No contact with any known illegal drug manufacturer or deliverer.
- No contact with Marvin S. (DOB 07-29-1987).
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with all child support court orders.
- Mental Health Evaluation and any recommended treatment. 
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Court does not impose DNA surcharge because of the date of the offense. 
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered.
